rest_of_day_open: I see myself trying to get through the week, by doing some arts and crafts and finding new shows to watch. I'll be getting my groceries through curbside and trying new recipes for food. I'll also be paying more attention to my pet to see if they are okay since they are sick.
critical_positive: I think the fact that they were on time to our conversation made me feel good. I always get a little put off when someone doesn't show up on time and thinks its okay. Also the fact that they were very kind and humble made it even better, because I like to talk to people who make an effort.
critical_negative: There wasn't anything I can say that didn't work well. other than maybe on my part I was scared at first to talk because I feel like I wouldn't have anything to talk about with an older man, but I messed up on my part for judging because they turned out to be good and friendly.

rest_of_day_open: Gonna be lean and worrisome. Really strapped right now. I'm trying to seek out alternate methods of obtaining groceries, but I'm not sure if it's going to work out. Difficult to get around in ubers. Gotta do something, because I think that the government is going to let us all starve.
critical_positive: I think it helped that we're both cat people who have been spending a lot of time indoors. We blew right past the 25 minute mark and ended up talking for over 45 minutes. I'm positive that she would've sat there and kept talking to me for another hour or more if I'd been amenable. I would've been. She was fun to talk to.
critical_negative: I think that I talked over her a little bit. Seemed like there were a couple of times where she couldn't hear what I said because I had spoken over her. It's my fault. I've got a bad "waiting to speak" habit. Comes from working in writer's rooms. You have to interrupt to get into the conversation. It's left me enfeebled socially.
